                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the east base of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Madhyasthanāthēśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Kulōttuṅga III. Year [20]: 1197-98 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>The donor figuring in this inscription is Puṇṇiyavāṭṭi, the mother of Āṟagaḷūruḍaiya Poṉparappiṉāṉ Rājarājadēvaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Magadēśaṉ, the well-known Bāṇa chief of Magadai-maṇḍalam.</p>						
                            
                            <p>It records a gift of income from taxes, including <hi rend="italic">āyam, antarāyam, pāḍikāval, taṟi-iṟai</hi>, and <hi rend="italic">śekkiṟaippāṭṭam</hi> on wet and dry lands in the village of Tiruppālaippandal to god Tirunāgīśuram-uḍaiya Nāyaṉār of the place, by the donor, mentioned above.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
